Exploratory Data Analysis on White Wine dataset¶

The aim of the project is to analyze different parameters affecting the quality of the white wine. We are given a White wine dataset and we must perform uni abd bivariate data analysis to depict how a content affects the quality. My project includes univarite analysis where i plot the featuresto check whether the data is normailzed or not.

bivariate:¶

The feature of data set is as follows. There are total of 12 variables .

!

Attribute information¶

  1. fixed acidity
  2. volatile acidity
  3. citric acid
  4. residual sugar
  5. chlorides
  6. free sulfur dioxide
  7. total sulfur dioxide
  8. density
  9. pH
  10. sulphates

  11. alcohol

    Output variable

  12. quality (score between 0 and 10)

Dataset Description¶

We are using White wine data set made on Portuguese "Vinho Verde " wine. The data set is available at This link The size of the data is 4898. It contains 11 features and 1 output column. The chemical properties like fixed acidity, volatile acidity , density and pH are all continuous data. The ouput , quality in a ordinal variable with ranking between 1-10. The data set contains no null values.

Univariate Analysis¶

Univariate analysis includes analysis of single features. It is used to check whether the feature is normally distributed or not and to find the outliers.

Inference from univariate analysis.¶

After plotting each of the graphs we can descide which are the strong features. The features with high mean and median are the one which affect the data the most. Those can be fixed cidity, residual sugar and pH. pH can also be a strong feature as it is the one which decides hte acidity content of. Alcohol content can play a major role in deciding the quality of the wine.

Furthure more strong features can be found using bivarite analysis.

Bivariate Analysis¶

in this we plot graph between two features to get a realtion between them. First of all we plot the correlation graph.

Quality vs Alcohol¶

In [29]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.regplot(x='quality', y='alcohol', data=df, x_jitter=0.3, scatter_kws={'alpha':0.2})
sns.despine()

The above plotting tells us that:

  1. Quality and Alcohol content are directly related.
  2. More the ALcohol, more the quality.
  3. The quality marked 6 have alcohol content between 9-11.
  4. The high quality wine have content more than 12.

Alcohol vs Density¶

The graph between alcohol and density is plotted below

In [100]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
sns.regplot(x='alcohol', y='density', data=df, x_jitter=0.2, scatter_kws={'alpha':0.15})
sns.despine()

These two are definitely correlated. More the density less the alcohol and vise versa.

So clearly Density and alcohol content are major features for our prediction. Now lets check how other features are related to these two.

Density vs Residual Sugar¶

The wines with high amount of residual sugar are more dense.

Inference from Bivariate data analysis.¶

The three main features were alcohol, density and chlorides. We can see that the the quality depends highly on alcohol content. And the alcohol content is inversly propostional to the density. Less density more the alcohol. One more feature that higly affect the data is of density and sugar. More residual sugar, more the density hence less alcohol content.

We have that density dont show much trend for low quality wines so we have to find more strog feature in multivariate analysis.

From the above 4 plots, we infer that:

Plot 1: Alcohol and density might be major features but the plotting of both dont show any major trend. Plot 2: For high quality of wine, the sulphuric acid must be low.

!!Plot 3 : The other main feature is the density which depeds on the residual sugar content. So less residual sugar, less density and more qaulity.

!!Plot 4: Now the sulphuric acid is always determined by pH content. so pH content should be between 3-3.5 and total sulphirc acid content should be low. This we can use as a main feature.

Summary:¶

After the analysis we came to know that the factors affecting the most are the total sulphur dioxied , the pH value , density and the alcohol content.

Plot 3 and plot 4 from multivariate analysis gives us the proof for the same. And the alcohol and Quality plot from the bivariate analysis gives us furthre proof.
